u Journal 9\n|\nSnape's patronus was a doe,' said Harry, 'the same as my mother's because he loved her for nearly all of his life, from when they were children.\n\n- J.K. Rowling, Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows\n|\nListen. Outside this frame I can see light,heavy as pardon, reliable as granite.Help me. Help me drag it into the picture.\n\n- Jeanne\n|\nWhat should be boundless is one's love of life, not one's love of art or knowledge.\n\n- Marty\n|\nTrue beauty is something that attacks, overpowers, robs, and finally destroys.\n\n- Yukio\n|\nWe are seeds as well as parasites to the earth. We can either give or take, depending on our perception of growth.\n\n- Zephyr\n|\nWhen we protect ourselves from what we fear, we also undermine our capacity for wonder.\n\n- Jonathan Martin, Prototype: What Happens When You Discover You're More Like Jesus Than You Think?\n|\nDepressing thought: my friends were the girls I ate lunch with, all buddies from kindergarten who knew one another so well we weren't sure if we even liked one another anymore.\n\n- Lauren Groff, Delicate Edible Birds and Other Stories\n|\n...it is precisely because the world appears to us to be multiple, ambiguous, and paradoxical, that we must strive to speak and write clearly.\n\n- Mark\n|\nWilliam: 'I'm sure we can all pull together, sir.'Vetinari: 'Oh, I do hope not. Pulling together is the aim of despotism and tyranny. Free men pull in all kinds of directions.\n\n- Terry Pratchett, The Truth\n|\nSmartass Disciple: Master, you keep preaching the truth. They don't listen.Master of Stupidity: Oh that's not bad. That attitude keeps us in the business.\n\n- Toba Beta, Master of Stupidity\n|\nHard work is the foundation of the abundant life, and sacrifice is needed to make it reality.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nDo you not think that God will protect us?”“No,” he said flatly. “My experience is that He rarely attends to the obvious.\n\n- Philippa Gregory, Changeling\n|\nI am joyfully responsible for myself, my own happiness, and creating a joyful life.\n\n- Amy Leigh Mercree, Joyful Living: 101 Ways to Transform Your Spirit and Revitalize Your Life\n|\nHow could we have found, who we really are, without education?\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nTo be truly great, begin to convert all your passing time into products through hard work.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nTout bonheur est un chef-d'oeuvre: la moindre erreur le fausse, la moindre hésitation l'altère, la moindre lourder le dépare, la moindre sottise l'abêtit.\n\n- Marguerite Yourcenar, Memoirs of Hadrian\n|\nI grew up once, I decided never to do it again\n\n- Benny Bellamacina, The King of Rhyme\n|\nWhen something looks impossible, don’t give up without testing its impossibility\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, Book of Wisdom\n|\nYour assumptions are your windows on the world. Scrub them off every once in a while, or the light won't come in.\n\n- Isaac\n|\nWhat is essential is to suddenly make a move totally unexpected by the opponent, pick up on the advantage of fright, and seize the victory right then and there.\n\n- Miyamoto Musashi, The Book of Five Rings\n|\nProducing what is required for the time, without damaging our inbuilt features is an art\n\n- Rajasaraswathii, I Want to be a Millionaire\n|\nImages barraged him. Connections darted electric. Veins. Roots. Forked lightning. Tributaries. Branches. Vines snaked around trees, herds of animals, drops of water running tog\n\n- Maggie Stiefvater, Blue Lily, Lily Blue\n|\nJust as music is noise that makes sense, a painting is colour that makes sense, so a story is life that makes sense.\n\n- Yann Martel, Beatrice and Virgil\n|\nEverything that humans have achieved until now, were once merely an imagination in someone’s head.\n\n- Abhijit\n|\nToo much sanity may be madness — and maddest of all: to see life as it is, and not as it should be!\n\n- Dale Wasserman, Man of La Mancha\n|\nThe key to a happy life is to have accomplishments to be proud of and purpose to look forward to, and at the moment I had both. How wonderful it was to be me.\n\n- Jeff Lindsay, Dearly Devoted Dexter\n|\nDo not, under any circumstances, put this book down and turn on the teevee.The teevee debilitates our culture.\n\n- Inga Muscio, Cunt: A Declaration of Independence\n|\nThe one thing I do remember is that as I retraced my steps through all the familiar streets of my life, Inow felt completely lost.\n\n- Carolyn Mackler, Vegan, Virgin, Valentine\n|\nWhen we lift our hands in praise and worship, we break spiritual jars of perfume over Jesus. The fragrance of our praise fills the whole earth and touches the heart of God.\n\n- Dennis\n|\nIf you want to be great, you must learn the secret of great men.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nConfidence is ignorance. If you're feeling cocky, it's because there's something you don't know.\n\n- Eoin Colfer, Artemis Fowl\n|\nThis is no occupation for an adult who can look other adults in the eye, carry his own weight, and count himself one of them.\n\n- Franz Wright, Kindertotenwald: Prose Poems\n|\nAll the lives I could live, all the people I will never know, never will be, they are everywhere. That is all that the world is.\n\n- Aleksandar Hemon, The Lazarus Project"